    "intitule": "Utilisation de la relation $\\tan\\alpha = \\frac{\\sin\\alpha}{\\cos\\alpha}$",
    "type": "ressource",
    "niveau": "medium",
    "enonce": {
      "texte": "<p>On donne $\\cos\\alpha = \\frac{3}{5}$ et $\\sin\\alpha = \\frac{4}{5}$.</p><p>1) Calculer $\\tan\\alpha$.<br>2) Vérifier que $\\tan^2\\alpha + 1 = \\frac{1}{\\cos^2\\alpha}$.</p>",
      "images": []
    },
    "questions": [
      {
        "numero": 1,
        "texte": "Calculer $\\tan\\alpha$.",
        "niveau": "medium",
        "reponse": "$\\tan\\alpha = \\frac{4}{3}$.",
        "sousQuestions": [
          {
            "numero": "1.a",
            "texte": "Rappeler la définition de $\\tan\\alpha$.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$\\tan\\alpha = \\frac{\\sin\\alpha}{\\cos\\alpha}$."
          },
          {
            "numero": "1.b",
            "texte": "Effectuer le calcul.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$\\tan\\alpha = \\frac{4/5}{3/5} = \\frac{4}{5} \\times \\frac{5}{3} = \\frac{4}{3}$."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "numero": 2,
        "texte": "Vérifier que $\\tan^2\\alpha + 1 = \\frac{1}{\\cos^2\\alpha}$.",
        "niveau": "medium",
        "reponse": "Calcul effectué : $\\tan^2\\alpha + 1 = (\\frac{4}{3})^2 + 1 = \\frac{16}{9} + 1 = \\frac{25}{9}$ et $\\frac{1}{\\cos^2\\alpha} = \\frac{1}{(3/5)^2} = \\frac{1}{9/25} = \\frac{25}{9}$. Les deux expressions sont égales.",
        "sousQuestions": [
          {
            "numero": "2.a",
            "texte": "Calculer $\\tan^2\\alpha + 1$.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$\\tan^2\\alpha + 1 = \\frac{16}{9} + 1 = \\frac{25}{9}$."
          },
          {
            "numero": "2.b",
            "texte": "Calculer $\\frac{1}{\\cos^2\\alpha}$.",
            "niveau": "medium",
            "reponse": "$\\frac{1}{\\cos^2\\alpha} = \\frac{1}{(3/5)^2} = \\frac{25}{9}$."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
